    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{-\frac{2r}{r^{2}+9r+20}-\frac{2r}{r+5}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{2r}{r+4}, r\ne -5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {-\frac{2r}{r^{2}+9r+20}-\frac{2r}{r+5}} 
      \amp = {-\frac{2r}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}-\frac{2r}{r+5}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{2r}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}-\frac{2r}{r+5}} \cdot \frac{(r+4)}{(r+4)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{2r}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}-\frac{2r\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-2r-2r\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-2r-2r^{2}-8r}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-2r^{2}-10r}{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-2r\mathopen{}\left(r+5\right)}}{{\left(r+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(r+4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{2r}{r+4}, r\ne -5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r+5</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {-5}</m>.</p>
</solution>
